		"title"		: "When A Dragon Moves In",
		"text"		: "1\n00:00:03,220 --> 00:00:07,900\nWelcome to Storyline Online brought to\nyou by the SAG-AFTRA Foundation.\n\n2\n00:00:07,900 --> 00:00:12,280\nMy name is Mark Duplass, and today we are going to be reading you the great book\n\n3\n00:00:13,460 --> 00:00:16,000\nWhen A Dragon Moves In\n\n4\n00:00:16,220 --> 00:00:19,600\nwritten by Jody Moore\nand illustrated by Howard McWilliam.\n\n5\n00:00:21,280 --> 00:00:25,000\nIf you build a perfect sandcastle,\n\n6\n00:00:27,380 --> 00:00:29,900\na dragon will move in.\n\n7\n00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:37,640\nHe'll settle in all cozy and peep at you from inside\n\n8\n00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:40,920\nand you'll wonder how you ever got\n\n9\n00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,140\nso lucky.\n\n10\n00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:48,960\nWith a dragon in your castle, you'll have a built-in marshmallow toaster,\n\n11\n00:00:49,740 --> 00:00:52,740\nyour very own raft,\n\n12\n00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:56,860\nand a kite that practically flies by itself.\n\n13\n00:00:58,280 --> 00:01:05,100\nBest of all, no beach bully would dare\nstomp your castle with a dragon inside.\n\n14\n00:01:06,460 --> 00:01:09,180\nOf course, there are rules on the beach,\n\n15\n00:01:10,140 --> 00:01:12,600\nso you'll have to hide his smoke from the lifeguard,\n\n16\n00:01:14,780 --> 00:01:17,720\nand erase the dragon\nprints from the sand.\n\n17\n00:01:21,740 --> 00:01:25,300\nEventually you'll want to share the great news with your family.\n\n18\n00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:29,340\n\"There's a dragon in my castle,\" you'll call to your mom.\n\n19\n00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:33,220\n\"Mmmm...hmmm,\" she'll answer.\n\n20\n00:01:33,220 --> 00:01:35,980\n\"Listen to him roar,\" you'll say.\n\n21\n00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:43,120\n\"I hear the roar of the ocean,\" she'll reply.\n\n22\n00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:51,100\n\"See this feather from my dragon's\nwing?\" you'll ask your dad.\n\n23\n00:01:51,660 --> 00:01:57,300\n\"That's a nice seagull feather,\" he'll say.\n\"And you know what feathers are good for.\"\n\n24\n00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:04,560\n\"Feel my dragon's sharp teeth!\" you'll shout.\n\n25\n00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:08,380\n\"Those are just broken shells,\" your big sister will say.\n\n26\n00:02:09,180 --> 00:02:13,414\nBut you and your dragon\nwill know better.\n\n27\n00:02:14,180 --> 00:02:17,760\nJust about then, your dragon will demand to be fed.\n\n28\n00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:22,380\nFirst he'll eat all the peanut butter sandwiches,\n\n29\n00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:28,700\neven the ones that were supposed to be\nfor your sister.\n\n30\n00:02:30,500 --> 00:02:34,520\nThen his fiery snout will make the lemonade\n\n31\n00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:38,920\nsiiiiiiiiiizzzzzzzzle.\n\n32\n00:02:40,060 --> 00:02:44,342\n\"Stop blowing bubbles in your drink,\" your mom will say.\n\n33\n00:02:44,342 --> 00:02:48,600\n\"That wasn't me,\" you'll answer.\n\"That was the dragon.\"\n\n34\n00:02:48,860 --> 00:02:56,440\nAnd you'll hear a heh-heh-heh from deep inside the sandcastle.\n\n35\n00:02:56,440 --> 00:03:02,200\nFinally since dragons love dessert, he'll slink into the family cooler\n\n36\n00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:05,780\nand nibble the brownies when no one is looking.\n\n37\n00:03:10,140 --> 00:03:15,620\n\"Whose fingerprints are in the brownies?\"\nyour dad will ask.\n\n38\n00:03:15,620 --> 00:03:20,180\n\"Not fingerprints,\" you'll try to explain. \"Dragon prints.\"\n\n39\n00:03:20,180 --> 00:03:25,160\n\"There's no such thing as a dragon,\" your sister will say.\n\n40\n00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:29,520\nThen your dragon will snicker again, heh-heh-heh...\n\n41\n00:03:30,740 --> 00:03:35,940\nand spray sand all over her.\n\n42\n00:03:36,460 --> 00:03:40,140\n\"Young man, I don't think this is funny,\" your mom will say.\n\n43\n00:03:40,140 --> 00:03:43,460\n\"That wasn't me,\" you'll answer.\n\n44\n00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:47,760\n\"It was the dragon.\"\n\n45\n00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:53,420\n\"I think we've had enough of this dragon business,\" your dad will say.\n\n46\n00:03:55,240 --> 00:04:01,840\n\"I guess I've had enough of this dragon\nbusiness too,\" you'll sigh.\n\n47\n00:04:05,700 --> 00:04:11,180\nThen you'll march over to your sandcastle \nand order your dragon to leave\n\n48\n00:04:11,980 --> 00:04:14,500\nuntil he learns some manners.\n\n49\n00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:18,200\nAnd you will vow\n\n50\n00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:22,260\nnever to build\n\n51\n00:04:22,260 --> 00:04:25,780\na perfect sandcastle\n\n52\n00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,640\nagain.\n\n53\n00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:47,600\nAt least until tomorrow.\n\n54\n00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:56,720\nThe end.\n\n55\n00:04:56,720 --> 00:05:01,680\nSo this is a book about the\npower of imagination and the power of\n\n56\n00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:07,440\nthose people around you who don't often\nhonor your imagination. And the important\n\n57\n00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:12,840\nthing here is that no matter what people\nsay, if you believe it in your mind if\n\n58\n00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:17,960\nyou can see it in your mind, you've got\nto hang on to it.\n\n59\n00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:25,400\nThank you for watching Storyline Online and make sure to check out all of our stories.\n\n60\n00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:28,640\nAnd don't forget to keep watching and keep reading.",
