		"title"		: "When Pigasso Met Mootisse",
		"text"		: "1\n00:00:04,140 --> 00:00:08,240\nHi, Welcome to SAG Foundation's BookPALS Storyline Online.\n\n2\n00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:18,099\nMy name is Eric Close, and today, I'm going to be reading \"When Pigasso met Mootisse,\" written and illustrated by Nina Laden.\n\n3\n00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:21,520\nThere once was a young pig named Pigasso.\n\n4\n00:00:21,520 --> 00:00:28,520\nWhile the other piglets rolled in the mud and played games, Pigasso painted.\n\n5\n00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:34,570\nHe painted anything and everything, and in a most unusual way.\n\n6\n00:00:34,570 --> 00:00:38,200\nAt the same time, there was a young bull named Mootisse.\n\n7\n00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:45,460\nMootisse was not like the other bulls. He wasn't interested in bull fighting.\n\n8\n00:00:45,460 --> 00:00:53,740\nMootisse was happy only when he painted pictures. And he painted big, bold, bright pictures.\n\n9\n00:00:54,870 --> 00:00:59,320\nIn time, word of Pigasso's talent spread throughout the pig provinces.\n\n10\n00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:05,000\nSoon, art loving pigs from all over lined up to buy his creations.\n\n11\n00:01:05,010 --> 00:01:09,080\nAt the same time, Mootisse was getting famous in the cattle community.\n\n12\n00:01:09,080 --> 00:01:13,580\nThere weren't many households that didn't own a \"Moosterpiece.\"\n\n13\n00:01:13,580 --> 00:01:20,259\nPigasso and Mootisse were becoming art superstars.  But this came with a price.\n\n14\n00:01:20,259 --> 00:01:27,080\nEverybody wanted to see them: art buyers, art sellers, art students, art historians, art groupies.\n\n15\n00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:29,220\nIt was an art attack!\n\n16\n00:01:29,220 --> 00:01:34,120\nOne day Pigasso got fed up and said, \"I'm tired of this noisy pig pen.\"\n\n17\n00:01:34,380 --> 00:01:39,400\nAt the same time Mootisse declared, \"I'm sick of this crowded cow town.\"\n\n18\n00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:46,900\nNeeding a change, they both decided to look for a peaceful place where they could paint without distractions.\n\n19\n00:01:47,650 --> 00:01:52,280\nSo each of the two artists looked far and wide for the perfect spot.\n\n20\n00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:56,000\nPigasso found a lovely farm looking towards the east.\n\n21\n00:01:56,010 --> 00:01:59,200\nMootisse found a handsome farm facing the west.\n\n22\n00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:04,740\nAfter Pigasso moved in, he went to introduce himself to his new neighbor across the road.\n\n23\n00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:09,640\nAt the same time, Mootisse went to introduce himself to his new neighbor across the road.\n\n24\n00:02:09,640 --> 00:02:14,919\nThat is how Pigasso met Mootisse.\n\n25\n00:02:14,919 --> 00:02:21,109\nAnd coincidentally, that is how Mootisse met Pigasso.\n\n26\n00:02:21,109 --> 00:02:26,200\nAt first, Pigasso and Mootisse were friendly and welcomed each other as neighbors.\n\n27\n00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:29,320\nBut soon, things began to change.\n\n28\n00:02:30,380 --> 00:02:35,660\nIt started one day when Pigasso criticized one of Mootisse's paintings.\n\n29\n00:02:35,660 --> 00:02:39,680\nThen Mootisse made fun of one of Pigasso's.\n\n30\n00:02:39,940 --> 00:02:46,049\nMootisse called Pigasso an \"Art Hog.\"  \nThen Pigasso called Mootisse a \"Mad Cow.\"\n\n31\n00:02:46,049 --> 00:02:53,759\nMootisse quipped, \"You paint like a two year old.\"\nPigasso retorted, \"You paint like a wild beast.\"\n\n32\n00:02:53,760 --> 00:03:01,240\nMootisse raged, \"Your colors look like mud.\" \nPigasso spat, \"Your paintings look like color-by-numbers!\"\n\n33\n00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:07,720\nThen things got really out of hand.\n\n34\n00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:11,820\nIt was a modern art mess.\n\n35\n00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:20,980\nPigasso stormed off into his house. \"That Mootisse doesn't like my art,\" he huffed. \"Well, I'll show him.\"\n\n36\n00:03:24,060 --> 00:03:30,600\nAnd Mootisse bullied his way into his house, \"I'll give that Pigasso something he can really criticize,\" he snorted.\n\n37\n00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:38,140\nThen a full-scale feud erupted. But it was a most unusual battle.\n\n38\n00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:42,880\nArmed with ladders and buckets of paint, Mootisse launched the first attack.\n\n39\n00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:51,440\nHe started at dawn. By the end of the evening he had succeeded in transforming the outside of his house into a monster-sized \"Moosterpiece.\"\n\n40\n00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:59,180\nNot to be outdone, Pigasso fired up his paint brushes and, in full view of the enemy, counter-attacked.\n\n41\n00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:03,860\nHe turned his farm into a huge and outrageous \"Pork of Art.\"\n\n42\n00:04:04,420 --> 00:04:09,140\nThe two artists then retreated into their houses and pulled down the shades.\n\n43\n00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:13,880\nPigasso certainly didn't want to look out his window and stare at a \"Mootisse.\"\n\n44\n00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:17,780\nAnd Mootisse had no desire to give his rooms a view of a \"Pigasso.\"\n\n45\n00:04:22,420 --> 00:04:28,160\nThis presented a problem. And there seemed to be only one solution.\n\n46\n00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:36,860\nWithout a word to each other, Pigasso and Mootisse each began to build a huge wooden fence down the middle of their road.\n\n47\n00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:44,960\nAt first, Pigasso and Mootisse seemed satisfied. Both artists went back to painting by themselves.\n\n48\n00:04:44,960 --> 00:04:51,639\nBut after awhile, Pigasso was surprised to find that he missed that bull-headed Mootisse.\n\n49\n00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:58,400\nAt the same time, Mootisse found his studio empty without the presence of pig-headed Pigasso.\n\n50\n00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:08,180\nPigasso pondered, \"That Mootisse isn't such a bad artist. He has some interesting ideas.\"\n\n51\n00:05:08,180 --> 00:05:17,420\nMootisse moaned, \"That Pigasso may not paint like me, but he knows what he's doing.\"\n\n52\n00:05:18,140 --> 00:05:26,280\nHowever, being naturally pig-headed and bull-headed, neither artist knew how to apologize to the other.\n\n53\n00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:31,360\nSo they did what they do best. They let their paint brushes do the talking.\n\n54\n00:05:32,009 --> 00:05:36,700\nPigasso painted on one side of the fence, and Mootisse painted on the other.\n\n55\n00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:40,200\nEach worked until they were exhausted.\n\n56\n00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:45,080\nIt was strangely quiet when they were done.\n\n57\n00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:52,860\nThen, curious to see what Mootisse had been doing, Pigasso sprinted around to the other side.\n\n58\n00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:57,300\nAt the same time, Mootisse galloped over to Pigasso's side.\n\n59\n00:05:57,300 --> 00:06:03,220\nThe silence was broken as the two artists began laughing at their amazing work of heart.\n\n60\n00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:08,380\nFrom that day on, Pigasso and Mootisse became great friends.\n\n61\n00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:13,110\nThey happily took down the fence and shared their different views.\n\n62\n00:06:13,110 --> 00:06:17,439\nA few months later, a big museum bought the fence.\n\n63\n00:06:17,439 --> 00:06:28,819\nPigasso called his side: \"When Pigasso Met Mootisse.\"  Mootisse called his side: \"When Mootisse Met Pigasso.\"\n\n64\n00:06:28,820 --> 00:06:33,280\nThe critics called it \"Incredible.\"\n\n65\n00:06:35,489 --> 00:06:43,740\nNow, Picasso and Matisse weren't actually a pig and a bull, they were really two of the greatest artists of the twentieth century.\n\n66\n00:06:43,749 --> 00:06:48,660\nWhen you get the chance, I really encourage you to go and check out their paintings in a museum.\n\n67\n00:06:48,660 --> 00:06:52,680\nThey are beautiful and I think you'll love them. Thanks for listening.",
