		"title"		: "Me and My Cat",
		"text"		: "1\n00:00:01,640 --> 00:00:08,629\nHello, I'm Elijah Wood. Welcome to the SAG Foundation Storyline.\n\n2\n00:00:08,629 --> 00:00:18,340\nI'll be reading a story today called \"Me and My Cat,\" by Satoshi Kitamura, both illustrated and written by, so let's get into it.\n\n3\n00:00:21,840 --> 00:00:26,800\nLate one night an old lady in a pointed hat came in through my bedroom window.\n\n4\n00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:32,940\nShe brandished her broom at me and fired out some words. Then she left without saying goodbye...\n\n5\n00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:37,510\n\"Nicholas, wake up! You'll be late for school.\"\n\n6\n00:00:37,510 --> 00:00:40,910\nIt must be mom. It must be morning again.\n\n7\n00:00:40,910 --> 00:00:48,080\nMom dragged me to the bathroom and made me wash and dress. Downstairs she interrupted my breakfast. She was furious.\n\n8\n00:00:48,080 --> 00:00:55,360\nShe carried me off to catch the school bus. I had gone... but I was still here...\n\n9\n00:00:55,370 --> 00:00:59,700\n\"How strange,\" I thought to myself, pulling my whiskers.\n\n10\n00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,480\nWHISKERS?!\n\n11\n00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:08,080\nI rushed to the bathroom and looked at myself in the mirror. Leonardo, my cat, was staring back at me.\n\n12\n00:01:08,080 --> 00:01:10,260\nBut it wasn't him inside.\n\n13\n00:01:10,260 --> 00:01:14,240\nIt was me, Nicholas! I couldn't believe my eyes.\n\n14\n00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:16,850\nI had turned into a cat!\n\n15\n00:01:16,850 --> 00:01:22,620\n\"Don't panic,\" I told myself. I sat in the armchair to consider the situation carefully...\n\n16\n00:01:22,620 --> 00:01:27,100\nI fell asleep. When I woke up, I felt a little better.\n\n17\n00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:31,960\nMaybe it wasn't such a bad thing to be a cat. I didn't have to go to school, did I?\n\n18\n00:01:31,960 --> 00:01:39,049\nI hopped onto the table, and from there to the top of the shelves. What fun! I could never do this before.\n\n19\n00:01:39,049 --> 00:01:47,140\nI decided to leap toward the cupboard on the other side of the room. Ready, set...  oops.\n\n20\n00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:49,740\nMom threw me out of the house.\n\n21\n00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:57,840\nWhile I was rambling in the garden, Gioconda, the next-door-neighbor cat, came up and licked me all over my face. Yuck!\n\n22\n00:01:57,840 --> 00:02:00,340\n\"Time to go for a walk,\" I thought.\n\n23\n00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:08,780\nThe brick wall was warm under my paws. As I got close to Miss Thomson's garden, a funny thought occurred to me.\n\n24\n00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:16,620\nMiss Thomson had given me Leonardo when he was a kitten. Leonardo was Heloise's son.\n\n25\n00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:20,760\nDid that mean Heloise was now my mother?\n\n26\n00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:27,900\n\"Miaow, Miam (Hello, Mom),\" I called tentatively. She ignored me completely.\n\n27\n00:02:27,909 --> 00:02:31,849\nFarther along, I came across three mean-looking cats.\n\n28\n00:02:31,849 --> 00:02:35,240\n\"Excuse me. May I go through?\" I said.\n\n29\n00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:38,760\n\"No, go away! It's our wall,\" replied one.\n\n30\n00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:44,640\n\"I think the wall belongs to every--\"\nBut before I could finish my sentence they were all over me.\n\n31\n00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:48,940\nWe punched and kicked and scratched one another until we fell off the wall, entangled.\n\n32\n00:02:48,940 --> 00:02:56,449\n\"Bowwowowowowowowow!\" A dog came running toward us, barking furiously. The cats ran away in all directions.\n\n33\n00:02:56,449 --> 00:03:02,579\nIt was Bernard, Mr. Stone's dog. He's a sweet dog, my favorite in the neighborhood.\n\n34\n00:03:02,620 --> 00:03:07,180\n\"Thanks, Bernard. You came just in time.\"  \nBut he chased me out of the garden.\n\n35\n00:03:07,180 --> 00:03:11,120\nOf course! He couldn't recognize me.\n\n36\n00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:18,080\nSo this was the world that Leonardo lived in. Life was as tough and complicated as it was for humans.\n\n37\n00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:23,200\nWhen I got home, I went into the house. Then I heard a scratching noise coming from the front door.\n\n38\n00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:28,600\nIt was \"me\" back from school, trying to get in through the cat flap.\n\n39\n00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:34,840\nBut was he me, \"Nicholas\"? Or was he poor little Leonardo inside my body?\n\n40\n00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:38,920\nOnce indoors, he continued to behave strangely.\n\n41\n00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:44,440\nHe scratched himself earnestly, and when that was done, he challenged his shoes until they surrendered.\n\n42\n00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:49,620\nHe licked his sweater clean, then spent a long time sharpening his nails.\n\n43\n00:03:49,620 --> 00:03:52,100\nHe found the goldfish particularly fascinating.\n\n44\n00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:56,220\nHe tried to sort the washing, and then the yarn... but at last he gave up.\n\n45\n00:03:56,220 --> 00:04:01,969\nHe found the radiator and the litter box irresistible.  But he didn't seen to like me at all.\n\n46\n00:04:01,969 --> 00:04:09,980\nAt last, Mom saw something was wrong with her son. She became so worried that she called the doctor and asked him to come at once.\n\n47\n00:04:10,620 --> 00:04:18,650\n\"Nothing to worry about,\" said Dr. Wire. \"He's just a little overtired. Send him to bed early and he'll be fine in the morning.\"\n\n48\n00:04:18,650 --> 00:04:26,349\nMom was still very upset.  She held him tight in her arms all evening.  I felt sorry for them both.\n\n49\n00:04:26,349 --> 00:04:35,060\nI climbed on Leonardo-in-my-shape and stroked his cheek. He purred. Then Mom stroked me gently. I purred.\n\n50\n00:04:35,060 --> 00:04:39,409\nLater that night, the old lady in the pointed hat came in through my bedroom window.\n\n51\n00:04:39,409 --> 00:04:42,780\n\"Sorry, love. I got the wrong address,\" she said.\n\n52\n00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:48,500\nShe brandished her broom and blurted out some words. Then she left without saying good night.\n\n53\n00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:53,620\n\"Nicholas, wake up! You'll be late for school,\" I heard Mom shouting.\n\n54\n00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:57,080\nEverything was back to normal.\n\n55\n00:04:57,080 --> 00:05:01,340\nAt school Mr. McGough sat on the table.\n\n56\n00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:08,460\nHe scratched himself, licked his shirt, and fell asleep for the rest of the lesson.\n\n57\n00:05:08,460 --> 00:05:13,080\nWell that's the end of our story.  It's been very enjoyable to sit here and read to you.\n\n58\n00:05:13,090 --> 00:05:20,949\nIf you'd like to rent this book from a library, then go to your local library and get this book and maybe you can read along with me.\n\n59\n00:05:20,949 --> 00:05:26,780\nYou can click on me and I'll read you the story and you can read the book with me. It should be quite enjoyable.\n\n60\n00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:28,120\nThank you very much.",
